Aare Akogun Muslumi of Oyo State, Hon. Idris Abolaji Abiola Ajimobi has condoled with the Muslim community and the Chief Imam of Ibadanland over the death of Bashir Busari Okunmebo, Chief Mufasir of Ogbomosho, The Grand Mufty of Oyo State. Ajimobi who’s currently performing his Hajj in Mecca described the death of the Chief Mufasir of Ogbomosho and the Grand Mufty of Oyo State as a great loss to the Muslim Community of Oyo State and Nigeria as a whole In a condolence message made available to journalists in Ibadan, he described the death of the Chief Mufasir of Ogbomosho as a great loss to the Muslim Community of the State and Nigeria as a whole. He noted that the deceased was like a father to him, stressing that he was going to miss him and his fatherly advice. The statement read,  Baba Mufasir was like a father to me, I’m going to miss his fatherly advice and preaches to me, moreover, I can never forget his role and impact on me during my turbaning as the Aare Akogun Muslumi of Oyo State, all the advises and the sermon he preached to me I won’t forget any. What else can we say to Almighty Allah, rather than to continue to seek for the forgiveness of our sins and that Almighty Allah should grant him Aljanat Firdaoz Amin.” Idris stated.